'''Ganton Scott''' (born in [[Toronto, Ontario]]) was a [[Canadian]] [[professional]] [[ice hockey|hockey]] [[winger (ice hockey)|right winger]] who played four seasons in the [[National Hockey League]] during the 1920s for the [[Toronto St. Pats]], [[Hamilton Tigers]], [[Montreal Maroons]] and [[Toronto Maple Leafs]].

